modules.description: This module provides a `reload` function to open or refresh a URI in a web browser, with options to control background execution, URI prefixing, and browser selection. It operates on string URIs and supports custom browser commands through the `Bos.Cmd.t` type. Concrete use cases include reloading a locally served web application during development or refreshing API documentation after updates, particularly when used with tools like `js_of_ocaml`.

This module provides command line options for configuring web browser behavior, including selecting a browser, enabling prefix mode, and running in the background. It works with `Cmdliner.Term.t` values to integrate with command line parsing. Concrete use cases include customizing browser launch arguments and controlling reload behavior from the command line.
